3720           // denominator.  Given that the denominator is positive, there are two
3721           // cases:
3722           //
3723           //  1. The numerator is positive. The result range is [0,C) and
3724           //     [0,C) u< (1 << ceilLogBase2(C)).
3725           //
3726           //  2. The numerator is negative. Then the result range is (-C,0] and
3727           //     integers in (-C,0] are either 0 or >u (-1 << ceilLogBase2(C)).
3728           //
3729           // Thus a lower bound on the number of sign bits is `TyBits -
3730           // ceilLogBase2(C)`.
